DataElement.preferredName: Food or Food Substance Product Material Code ISO21090.CD.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A substance consumed by a human or animal for nutritional purposes. EXAMPLE(S): broccoli, donuts, pet treats A coded value specifying the non-unique textual identifier for the material. EXAMPLE(S): aspirin, tobacco, caffeine NOTE(S): The granularity of the code may vary depending on the specificity of the material. For example, acetaminophen, Tylenol, Tylenol 250 mg gel cap.
